# Unity C# Development Rules

## Version and target

- Unity **6.x**
- WebGL target unless module is explicitly platform-specific
- Reuse `unity/shared_bridge/` ‚Äî no duplicate bridge per game
- Portrait (1080√ó1920) or landscape (1920√ó1080) per game configuration

## C# standards

- PascalCase for classes and public members
- camelCase for local variables and parameters
- `_camelCase` for private serialized fields where adopted
- Explicit access modifiers; `readonly` where possible
- Interfaces for replaceable systems
- ScriptableObjects for approved configuration
- Assembly definitions for module boundaries
- XML documentation for public shared APIs where useful

